The paper discusses cooperative communication in wireless networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of MIMO precoder designs and MMSE-SIC receivers suggests a focus on signal processing (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a new protocol and compares it to conventional baselines, indicating a potential fit for computer communications (cs.COM).
